<subSubSection id="CEEB93E400EDEC0207A5E746E75DF226" pageId="0" pageNumber="205" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7CB78921B94DDB3B2712812B75C749E2" pageId="0" pageNumber="205">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="06542E103546F9409B9A3D90C7BE26D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="205">Rostrum width less than one-third of interorbital length, bifurcated, base elongated, fused, diverging abruptly forming a Y-shape, ending in acute tip. Pleonal somite II with one spine or tubercle. Merus of second pereopod smooth.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
